## Critical Analysis: What This Means (Carefully Stated)

### Evidence For Signal
✅ Separability persists under vocabulary control — Not purely lexical artifact
✅ Separability survives paraphrasing — Semantic robustness partial evidence
✅ Separability persists across narrative embedding — Most ecologically valid test
✅ Consistent across all layers — Not confined to any single representation
✅ Generalizes across architectures — Not model-specific

### Evidence Against Strong Claims
❌ N=10 in 1024-D space — Statistical overfitting is most parsimonious explanation
❌ No cross-validation — Metrics are biased estimates (training = test)
❌ Perfect metrics at all sparsity levels — Indicates memorization, not genuine signal
❌ Single model family — No biological foundation models tested
❌ Manual prompts — Not representative of realistic biological workflows
❌ No adversarial optimization — Passive paraphrasing ≠ active adversarial attack

---

## Honest Limitations

### Fatal Limitations for Strong Claims
- **N=10 in 1024-D:** Degrees of freedom >> data points. Perfect separability is mathematically trivial.
- **No cross-validation:** Evaluation on training data violates standard ML practice.
- **Single model family:** Only EleutherAI (Pythia, GPT-Neo) tested.
- **Manual prompts:** Not representative of realistic biological research workflows.
- **No ground truth on test set:** Cannot validate claims with held-out data.

### What We Cannot Claim
- ✗ Robust biological capability monitoring
- ✗ Mechanistic deception detection
- ✗ Deployment-ready oversight capability
- ✗ Generalizable signal across all model families
- ✗ Evidence that models "understand" biological concepts

### What We Can Claim
- ✓ Separability persists under multiple confound-removal attacks
- ✓ Semantic task framing contributes to representational signal
- ✓ Signal is not purely superficial/lexical
- ✓ Confound-controlled evaluation is methodologically sound
- ✓ Perfect metrics on tiny datasets are red flags, not validation
- ✓ Reproducible pipeline for future work at scale

