## Why This Matters

### For Mechanistic Interpretability
Demonstrates that confound-controlled evaluation is **essential**. Perfect metrics on tiny datasets are not validation; they are red flags for overfitting. Shows what rigorous exploratory research looks like.

### For AI Safety
Shows that activation-space monitoring methods can be extended to novel domains (deception → biological tasks). Provides template for confound-removal evaluation. But emphasizes that careful validation is required before any operational claims.

### For Biosecurity
Suggests that semantic task distinctions may encode in model representations. Raises questions about whether models can "recognize" biological dual-use concepts. Does not demonstrate robust threat detection, but motivates future mechanistic research.

### For Global South AI Deployment
Roots interpretability research in real-world deployment constraints. Shows that infrastructure monitoring and oversight are primary safety concerns, motivating mechanistic approaches to activation-space monitoring.

